sec.p:
In this numerical exploration, the dynamics of two-dimensional, steady-state, incompressible and electrically conducted flow of ethylene glycol-based hybrid nanofluid over an exponentially stretchable sheet under the stimulus of partial slip and thermal jump conditions are examined. The base fluid i.e., ethylene glycol is hybridized by immersing very fine nanoparticles of molybdenum disulfide (MoS2) and graphene into the fluid. For the development of the mathematical model, the Cartesian coordinate system is considered where the x-axis is allied with the surface of the stretchable sheet, the y-axis is taken in a perpendicular direction and the flow-field is constrained to y>0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$y > 0$$\end{document}. A physical diagram of the problem is exhibited in Fig. 1. The following assumptions are made to obtain the governing equations for the dynamics of hybrid nanofluid flow:
